.TH AURA\-TESTING 7 "2026-04-19" "Aura 0.1.0" "Aura Manual"
.SH NAME
aura\-testing \- testing conventions, fakes, and feature\-file organization
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gleam test
.br
.B gleam run \-m features/runner
.br
.B gleam test \-\-tag @slow
.RI "(future)"
.br
.B gleam test \-\-contract
.RI "(future)"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Aura's test suite is built on two frameworks with a hard separation between
what each covers.
.PP
.B gleeunit
(the Gleam standard test framework) owns all unit tests in
.IR test/aura/ .
These tests exist today and cover individual modules in isolation: pure
functions, actor state machines, data transformations.
.PP
.B dream_test
owns all behavior tests in
.IR test/features/ .
These tests run Gherkin
.I .feature
files through a composed step registry.
They exercise complete workflows: a user message arrives, a real BEAM
supervision subtree processes it using faked external clients, and the
outcome is asserted on the fake's event log.
.PP
The separation is permanent.
Migrating unit tests to dream_test would be weeks of mechanical work with
silent-regression risk and no gain.
Each test fits the framework that makes its intent clearest.
.SS Two\-layer model
.TP
.B Behavior tests
Does my code do the right thing?
Unit tests of pure functions and integration tests of actors running in a
real BEAM with faked network boundaries.
Fast, deterministic.
This is the bulk of the suite.
.TP
.B Contract tests
Does the external world behave as assumed?
Live calls to z.ai, Discord, Google, Jira.
Run on demand.
A failure means a provider changed something, not that we broke.
.TP
.B Fault\-injection tests
Does my code recover when things break?
A named subset of behavior tests.
Inject stream stalls, worker crashes, malformed responses.
Tagged
.B @fault\-injection
so they can be counted and audited; included in the default run.
.PP
These categories come from principle #9 in
.IR docs/ENGINEERING.md .
Principle #10 requires every feature to ship with a behavior test that
fails without the change and passes with it.
The trivial-test hook (see
.BR HOOKS )
enforces this mechanically.
